                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/3312a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to President
                            <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 2, 1917</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: I send you some thoughts<note
                        n="90" xml:id="d557fn1">There are no enclosures with the file copy of this
                        letter; the reference is probably to the following document.</note> on
                    Germany’s broken promise and the crime of submarine warfare, which I put down in
                    writing last evening. These express my real views, which of course are given no
                    publicity.</p>
                <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
